Use pickle module to read to file( Unpickle function in utils.py with <name> in {hdm_h_ll_z_inv,zz_ll_inv}) 

It is a python dictionary containing (parton-level)Leptons and Inv(neutrinos) with (10000,2) dimensional numpy arrays
for 10000 events with 2 leptons(charged and neutral) in each event, each of these entries are TLorentzVectors 
Requires pyROOT>=6.04 ( it can be installed with: conda install -c conda-forge root # may clash with preinstalled root!!)

Put these two pickle files in ./passed_events in the working directory
Use data_convert.py to extract csv files
